    "body": "### Problem\n\nAs discovered by a matrix user, creating a language mapping between a single-byte (`from`) and multi-byte (`to`) character trips an assertion in `did_set_langmap`:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/80a8c3d23baeaa69b99b6871f5d5f03c3adb0ae0/src/nvim/mapping.c#L2607\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vim\nset langmap=eÑ‘\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo assertion; Vim lacks the `assert` and happily narrows `to` to `char_u`. (a bug? `langmap_mapchar` needs to be an array of `int`? I don't know enough about `&langmap` ðŸ¤·)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1909+g922816877f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, 9.1.2028 (but probably yes if ignoring the `assert`)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora Workstation 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
